gadi","key":"rangadi","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Raghu Angadi","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"created":"2009-01-08T01:03:05.194+0000","updated":"2009-01-08T01:03:05.194+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12411538/comment/12661817","id":"12661817","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rangadi","name":"rangadi","key":"rangadi","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Raghu Angadi","active":true,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"body":"Regd testing the feature :\n\nI have manually tested this by introducing an explicit delay once in a while in offerService() at the datanode.\n\nAlso modified heartbeats interval to be very low so that I can keep block report interval to be just a few seconds. \n\nSay block report interval is 4 seconds.\n\nWithout the patch : When the delay of 10 seconds occurs t, subsequent block reports occur at  t+14, t+18 etc.\n\nWith the patch : subsequent reports occur at t+12, t+16, t+20.\n\nThis confirms that if such a delay were to occur at the many datanodes at the same time, their subsequent blockreport occur based on what the intitial blockReport time was rather than when the delay ended.\n\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rangadi","name":"rangadi","key":"rangadi","avat